{"type":"message","id":"3e5eef8c","parentId":"2ade5ab6","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:30:24.196Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The Daily Station Check failed again — \"cron: job execution timed out\n(last phase: model-call-started).\" This has been \"fixed\" three times\nand it's still burning tokens on model calls.\n\nSTOP PATCHING THIS. Find the root cause:\n\n1. Is there a SECOND cron job still active that we missed? The old\n dae7406b was supposedly disabled. Is there another one?\n\n2. The new LaunchAgent (com.openclaw.daily-station-check) was supposed\n to be shell-only. Is it actually running? Or is the old cron still\n firing?\n\n3. Run: openclaw cron list\n Show me EVERY cron job. Not just the ones you think are active.\n All of them.\n\n4. If the old cron is still there and enabled, DELETE it. Not disable.\n DELETE.\n\n5. If the new LaunchAgent is the one failing, read its payload. Find\n what's triggering model-call-started. Remove it.\n\nThis has burned tokens on three separate days now. Fix it permanently\nor delete the daily check entirely. A broken job is worse than no job.","timestamp":1780295424110}}
