{"type":"message","id":"02e0ae35","parentId":"8cb69d4d","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:31:57.051Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed. Here's the full debrief:\n\n**Root cause:** The old OpenClaw cron job `dae7406b` (\"Daily Station Check\") was **never actually disabled or deleted** when we switched to the LaunchAgent. It was an `agentTurn` job — meaning it spawned an isolated AI session every night at 11pm. The prompt explicitly said \"do NOT use any AI model calls\" but it was still an `agentTurn` payload, so OpenClaw always started a model session. The model would begin its call, then hit the 120s timeout while still in `model-costing tokens every time.\n\nThe LaunchAgent (`com.openclaw.daily-station-check`) was correctly set up as shell-only and was working fine in parallel — it's the one that successfully sent the sitrep you saw (`✅ Sent via telegram. Message ID: 2326`).\n\n**What I did:** Permanently **deleted** cron job `dae7406b` — not disabled, deleted.\n\n**Current cron state:** 3 jobs remaining, all healthy:\n| Job | Schedule | Status |\n|-----|----------|--------|\n| Sessions Cleanup | 2am UTC | ✅ Consecutive OK |\n| Session Auto-Expiry | 4am UTC | ✅ Consecutive OK |\n| Auto-update FreeRide | 6am BST | ✅ Consecutive OK |\n\n**The duplicate situation is gone.** Only the shell-based LaunchAgent runs the daily check now. Zero model calls, zero token burn.\n\nThis is on me — when we set up the LaunchAgent replacement, I should have deleted the cron immediately instead of leaving it \"disabled\" (which apparently didn't stick, or I never actually disabled it). Won't happen again. 🐒"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1498,"output":375,"cacheRead":24832,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":26705,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780295495327,"responseId":"gen-1780295495-Dvrz2XQA6l3IQdN4xObv"}}
{"type":"message","id":"87112cde-22f1-444a-8573-737408574386","parentId":"02e0ae35","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:31:58.331Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed. Here's the full debrief:\n\n**Root cause:** The old OpenClaw cron job `dae7406b` (\"Daily Station Check\") was **never actually disabled or deleted** when we switched to the LaunchAgent. It was an `agentTurn` job — meaning it spawned an isolated AI session every night at 11pm. The prompt explicitly said \"do NOT use any AI model calls\" but it was still an `agentTurn` payload, so OpenClaw always started a model session. The model would begin its call, then hit the 120s timeout while still in `model-costing tokens every time.\n\nThe LaunchAgent (`com.openclaw.daily-station-check`) was correctly set up as shell-only and was working fine in parallel — it's the one that successfully sent the sitrep you saw (`✅ Sent via telegram. Message ID: 2326`).\n\n**What I did:** Permanently **deleted** cron job `dae7406b` — not disabled, deleted.\n\n**Current cron state:** 3 jobs remaining, all healthy:\n| Job | Schedule | Status |\n|-----|----------|--------|\n| Sessions Cleanup | 2am UTC | ✅ Consecutive OK |\n| Session Auto-Expiry | 4am UTC | ✅ Consecutive OK |\n| Auto-update FreeRide | 6am BST | ✅ Consecutive OK |\n\n**The duplicate situation is gone.** Only the shell-based LaunchAgent runs the daily check now. Zero model calls, zero token burn.\n\nThis is on me — when we set up the LaunchAgent replacement, I should have deleted the cron immediately instead of leaving it \"disabled\" (which apparently didn't stick, or I never actually disabled it). Won't happen again. 🐒"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"total":0,"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":0,"total_tokens":0,"cache":{"read":0,"write":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780295518327}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc36dba0","parentId":"87112cde-22f1-444a-8573-737408574386","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:36:26.695Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The old cron is finally deleted. Confirmed: the LaunchAgent was working\ncorrectly the whole time — Message ID 2326 was the real sitrep.\n\nThree questions to close this out:\n\n1. The error feed shows this as INVESTIGATING with 1 consecutive error.\n Clear it — mark it resolved since the root cause (duplicate cron)\n is fixed.\n\n2. Add to FRAMEWORK.md gotchas: \"When replacing a cron job with a\n LaunchAgent, DELETE the old cron immediately. Do not disable —\n DELETE. Verify with openclaw cron list. The Daily Station Check\n burned tokens for 10+ days because dae7406b was left as agentTurn\n alongside the new shell-only LaunchAgent.\"\n\n3. Log this as an incident (if not already logged): INC-0XX — Daily\n Station Check duplicate cron causing nightly token burn from\n May 21-31. Root cause: agentTurn cron dae7406b not deleted when\n LaunchAgent replacement was created.","timestamp":1780295786616}}
