{"type":"message","id":"70d5c913","parentId":"c106b6d7","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:38:22.433Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"5e5ffaa8-f100-4db3-80a3-e9894760d67d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/cron-errors.ts"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/api/cron-errors.ts\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":359,"output":36,"cacheRead":41088,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":41483,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780295890727,"responseId":"gen-1780295890-NAZpApR6MSXDsWuNOvnz"}}
{"type":"message","id":"725c0137","parentId":"70d5c913","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:38:22.464Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"5e5ffaa8-f100-4db3-80a3-e9894760d67d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// src/routes/api/cron-errors.tsx\n// API route for fetching and updating cron error statuses\nimport { readFileSync, writeFileSync, existsSync, mkdirSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { join } from \"node:path\";\n\nconst WORKSPACE = process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE || \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace\";\n\nexport async function GET() {\n  try {\n    const errorsPath = join(WORKSPACE, \"data\", \"cron-errors.json\");\n    if (!existsSync(errorsPath)) {\n      return new Response(JSON.stringify([]), { headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" } });\n    }\n    const errors = JSON.parse(readFileSync(errorsPath, \"utf-8\"));\n    return new Response(JSON.stringify(errors), { headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" } });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return new Response(JSON.stringify([]), { headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" } });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function POST({ request }: { request: Request }) {\n  try {\n    const { errorId, status } = (await request.json()) as { errorId: string; status: string };\n    const errorsPath = join(WORKSPACE, \"data\", \"cron-errors.json\");\n    const dir = join(WORKSPACE, \"data\");\n    if (!existsSync(dir)) mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n    let errors: Record<string, unknown>[] = [];\n    try {\n      errors = JSON.parse(readFileSync(errorsPath, \"utf-8\"));\n    } catch {\n      /* empty */\n    }\n    const idx = errors.findIndex((e) => e.id === errorId);\n    if (idx !== -1) {\n      errors[idx].status = status;\n      errors[idx].updatedAt = new Date().toISOString();\n    } else {\n      errors.push({ id: errorId, status, updatedAt: new Date().toISOString() });\n    }\n    writeFileSync(errorsPath, JSON.stringify(errors, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ ok: true }), { headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" } });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"[api/cron-errors] Error:\", err);\n    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ ok: false, error: String(err) }), {\n      status: 500,\n      headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    });\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780295902463}}
{"type":"message","id":"633d64a0","parentId":"725c0137","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:38:42.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK — the cron-errors API reads from `cron-errors.json` and all entries are already `resolved`. The \"INVESTIGATING with 1 consecutive error\" Andre saw was likely the cron job's **own state** in the OpenClaw cron scheduler UI (the job itself showing `consecutiveErrors: 4`). Since I deleted it, that's gone. But let me also check what the error feed page actually renders — there might be a derived \"investigating\" status from the incidents:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"7e876c15-fb68-4104-87d4-89351706c7fb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"investigating\\|INVESTIGATING\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/ --include=\"*.ts\" --include=\"*.tsx\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -r \\\"investigating\\\\|INVESTIGATING\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/ --include=\\\"*.ts\\\" --include=\\\"*.tsx\\\" 2>/dev/null\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":670,"output":167,"cacheRead":41344,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":42181,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780295902467,"responseId":"gen-1780295902-BuBDHL06BtwSX7RqDcef"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d3fabfd2","parentId":"633d64a0","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:38:42.280Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"7e876c15-fb68-4104-87d4-89351706c7fb","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts:    // When investigating, auto-create a task on the Tasks page\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/incidents.tsx:  MITIGATING: { color: \"bg-violet/15 text-violet border-violet/30\", label: \"INVESTIGATING\" },\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/scheduler.tsx:                  {isInProgress && <Pill variant=\"violet\">INVESTIGATING</Pill>}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":42,"aggregated":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts:    // When investigating, auto-create a task on the Tasks page\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/incidents.tsx:  MITIGATING: { color: \"bg-violet/15 text-violet border-violet/30\", label: \"INVESTIGATING\" },\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/scheduler.tsx:                  {isInProgress && <Pill variant=\"violet\">INVESTIGATING</Pill>}","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780295922280}}
{"type":"message","id":"1fda82c6","parentId":"d3fabfd2","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:38:58.317Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There it is. Thescheduler page shows \"INVESTIGATING\" for in-progress items. This is the cron job's own card in the Mission Control dashboard. Since the job is **deleted**, it won't render anymore. But let me also check the `useCronData` to be sure it's not caching:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4d090b26-dbae-469f-84dd-c00c18bed689","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":351,"output":101,"cacheRead":41984,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":42436,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780295922281,"responseId":"gen-1780295922-ZlmErbzSd4oKjPTjB4yj"}}
{"type":"message","id":"533a24ae","parentId":"1fda82c6","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:38:58.330Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"4d090b26-dbae-469f-84dd-c00c18bed689","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { useState, useCallback, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport type { OpenClawCronJob } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\n\n// ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport interface CronError {\n  id: string;\n  jobName: string;\n  jobId: string;\n  jobEnabled: boolean;\n  consecutiveErrors: number;\n  lastError: string;\n  lastErrorReason: string;\n  lastRunAt: string;\n  status: \"new\" | \"in_progress\" | \"completed\" | \"skipped\";\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface CronData {\n  jobs: OpenClawCronJob[];\n  errors: CronError[];\n  loading: boolean;\n  toggling: string | null;\n  result: { id: string; message: string } | null;\n  fetchCrons: () => void;\n  handleToggle: (job: OpenClawCronJob) => Promise<void>;\n  updateErrorStatus: (errorId: string, newStatus: CronError[\"status\"]) => void;\n}\n\n// ── Hook ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function useCronData(): CronData {\n  const [jobs, setJobs] = useState<OpenClawCronJob[]>([]);\n  const [errors, setErrors] = useState<CronError[]>([]);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [toggling, setToggling] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [result, setResult] = useState<{ id: string; message: string } | null>(null);\n\n  const fetchCrons = useCallback(() => {\n    // Fetch both cron jobs and saved error statuses in parallel\n    Promise.all([\n      fetch(\"/api/crons\").then((res) => res.json()),\n      fetch(\"/api/cron-errors\").then((res) => res.json()).catch(() => []),\n    ])\n      .then(([cronJobsData, savedErrors]) => {\n        const cronJobs = cronJobsData as OpenClawCronJob[];\n        setJobs(cronJobs);\n\n        const savedMap = new Map(\n          (savedErrors as Record<string, unknown>[]).map((e) => [e.id, e.status as CronError[\"status\"]])\n        );\n\n        // Extract errors from jobs, merge with saved statuses\n        // Use job ID directly as the error key (deduped by construction since we filter\n        // unique jobs). Prefix with \"cron-err-\" to avoid collisions with other entities.\n        const errorItems: CronError[] = cronJobs\n          .filter((j) => (j.consecutiveErrors ?? 0) > 0 || j.status === \"error\")\n          .map((j) => {\n            const id = `cron-err-${j.id}`;\n            const savedStatus = savedMap.get(id) || savedMap.get(`err-${j.id}`); // also check legacy key\n            // Determine the effective status:\n            // - If job is still failing AND was previously investigated → keep in_progress\n            // - If job is still failing AND was resolved/skipped → the fix didn't work,\n            //   show as \"new\" again (re-escalate)\n            // - If job is still failing with no saved status → show as \"new\"\n            let status: CronError[\"status\"] = \"new\";\n            if (savedStatus === \"in_progress\") {\n              status = \"in_progress\"; // preserve investigation state\n            }\n            // Note: completed/skipped are intentionally NOT preserved here.\n            // If the job fails again after being resolved, it shows as a new error.\n            // This is the correct behavior — the previous resolution didn't fix it.\n            return {\n              id,\n              jobName: j.name,\n              jobId: j.id,\n              jobEnabled: j.enabled,\n              consecutiveErrors: j.consecutiveErrors ?? 0,\n              lastError: j.lastError ?? \"\",\n              lastErrorReason: j.lastErrorReason ?? \"\",\n              lastRunAt: j.lastRun,\n              status,\n              createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n            };\n          })\n          // Only show errors that are new or in_progress (not completed/skipped)\n          .filter((e) => e.status === \"new\" || e.status === \"in_progress\");\n\n        // Auto-clear + merge: remove errors whose jobs have recovered\n        // (consecutiveErrors === 0 and status !== \"error\"), merge existing\n        // in-memory statuses with fresh data, and add any new errors.\n        const activeErrorJobIds = new Set(errorItems.map((e) => e.jobId));\n        setErrors((prev) => {\n          const freshIds = new Set(errorItems.map((e) => e.id));\n          const prevIds = new Set(prev.map((e) => e.id));\n\n          // Start with existing errors: keep only those still active,\n          // merging fresh data while preserving in-memory status\n          const merged = prev\n            .filter((e) => {\n              if (freshIds.has(e.id)) return true; // still failing, in fresh list\n              if (!activeErrorJobIds.has(e.jobId)) return false; // job recovered → auto-clear\n              return true;\n            })\n            .map((e) => {\n              const fresh = errorItems.find((f) => f.id === e.id);\n              return fresh ? { ...fresh, status: e.status } : e;\n            });\n\n          // Add any brand-new errors not in previous state\n          const mergedIds = new Set(merged.map((e) => e.id));\n          const newItems = errorItems.filter((e) => !mergedIds.has(e.id) && !prevIds.has(e.id));\n\n          return [...merged, ...newItems];\n        });\n\n        setLoading(false);\n      })\n      .catch((err) => {\n        console.error(\"[SchedulerPage] Failed to fetch crons:\", err);\n        setLoading(false);\n      });\n  }, []);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    fetchCrons();\n    const interval = setInterval(fetchCrons, 5000);\n    return () => clearInterval(interval);\n  }, [fetchCrons]);\n\n  const handleToggle = useCallback(async (job: OpenClawCronJob) => {\n    setToggling(job.id);\n    setResult(null);\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch(\"/api/cron-toggle\", {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify({ id: job.id, action: job.enabled ? \"disable\" : \"enable\" }),\n      });\n      const data = await res.json();\n      if (data.ok) {\n        setJobs((prev) =>\n          prev.map((j) =>\n            j.id === job.id ? { ...j, enabled: !job.enabled } : j\n          )\n        );\n        setResult({ id: job.id, message: data.message || (job.enabled ? \"Disabled\" : \"Enabled\") });\n      } else {\n        setResult({ id: job.id, message: `Failed: ${data.error || \"Unknown error\"}` });\n      }\n    } catch (err) {\n      setResult({ id: job.id, message: `Failed: ${err}` });\n    }\n    setToggling(null);\n    setTimeout(() => setResult(null), 3000);\n  }, []);\n\n  const updateErrorStatus = useCallback((errorId: string, newStatus: CronError[\"status\"]) => {\n    const error = errors.find((e) => e.id === errorId);\n    // If completing or skipping, remove from feed immediately (don't wait for next poll)\n    if (newStatus === \"completed\" || newStatus === \"skipped\") {\n      setErrors((prev) => prev.filter((e) => e.id !== errorId));\n    } else {\n      setErrors((prev) =>\n        prev.map((e) =>\n          e.id === errorId ? { ...e, status: newStatus } : e\n        )\n      );\n    }\n    // Persist to server\n    fetch(\"/api/cron-errors\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ errorId, status: newStatus }),\n    }).catch((err) => console.error(\"[SchedulerPage] Failed to save error status:\", err));\n\n    // When investigating, auto-create a task on the Tasks page\n    if (newStatus === \"in_progress\" && error) {\n      const taskTitle = `[Investigate] ${error.jobName}: ${error.lastErrorReason || error.lastError}`;\n      const task = {\n        id: `task-err-${Date.now().toString(36)}`,\n        title: taskTitle,\n        assignee: \"monkey\",\n        status: \"in_progress\",\n        priority: \"P2\",\n        ts: \"just now\",\n        note: `Auto-created from Scheduler Error Feed.\\nCron job: ${error.jobName} (${error.jobId})\\nError: ${error.lastError}\\nConsecutive errors: ${error.consecutiveErrors}`,\n        history: [{\n          ts: new Date().toISOString(),\n          action: \"created\",\n          actor: \"system\",\n          details: `Auto-created from error feed for ${error.jobName}`,\n        }],\n        errorId: errorId,\n        jobId: error.jobId,\n      };\n      fetch(\"/api/tasks/add\", {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify(task),\n      }).then((res) => res.json()).then((data) => {\n        if (data.ok) {\n          console.log(\"[SchedulerPage] Created investigation task:\", taskTitle);\n        } else {\n          console.error(\"[SchedulerPage] Failed to create task:\", data.message);\n        }\n      }).catch((err) => console.error(\"[SchedulerPage] Failed to create task:\", err));\n    }\n\n    // When marking resolved, update the error status to completed\n    if (newStatus === \"completed\" && error) {\n      console.log(\"[SchedulerPage] Error marked as completed:\", error.jobName);\n    }\n  }, [errors]);\n\n  return {\n    jobs,\n    errors,\n    loading,\n    toggling,\n    result,\n    fetchCrons,\n    handleToggle,\n    updateErrorStatus,\n  };\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780295938329}}
{"type":"message","id":"c49f632b","parentId":"533a24ae","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:39:25.412Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full picture. The error feed in Mission Control reads from the cron API — since I deleted the job, it won't appear anymore. But the error might persist in the in-memory state until the polling cycle picks it up. Let me handle all three tasks now:\n\n**Q1: Clear the error feed** — the deleted job will naturally disappear from the feed on next poll (every 5s). But I should also navigate the UI to dismiss it if it's cached. Since this is likely Andre viewing it in the dashboard right now, the simplest fix is to trigger a clear via the API:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"cea2fc00-c84c-43cf-8f22-1549d476e75e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# The cron job is deleted and all cron-errors.json entries are resolved.\n# Let's also check if there's a specific \"investigating\" status entry for dae7406b\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\nerrors = json.load(open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/cron-errors.json'))\nfor e in errors:\n    if 'dae7406b' in str(e) or 'station' in str(e).lower() or 'daily' in str(e).lower():\n        print(json.dumps(e, indent=2))\n\"","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# The cron job is deleted and all cron-errors.json entries are resolved.\\n# Let's also check if there's a specific \\\"investigating\\\" status entry for dae7406b\\npython3 -c \\\"\\nimport json\\nerrors = json.load(open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/cron-errors.json'))\\nfor e in errors:\\n    if 'dae7406b' in str(e) or 'station' in str(e).lower() or 'daily' in str(e).lower():\\n        print(json.dumps(e, indent=2))\\n\\\"\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":2359,"output":269,"cacheRead":42240,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":44868,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780295938333,"responseId":"gen-1780295938-X8Z4WX0m3ojBmlEtGwSF"}}
