{"type":"message","id":"af8a6065","parentId":"6ea764e7","timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:26:21.330Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Column 141 is `)` and column 142 is `}`. The error says `}` expected at column 141. This means the parser encountered `)` where it expected `}`. \n\nThe issue is the double `))` at the end — `</div>))`. The first `)` closes the `.map()` and the second `)` closes... wait, let me look at the full expression:\n\n```\n{POSES.map(p => <div key={p} style={{...}}>{p}</div>))}\n```\n\nThat's `{POSES.map(...)}` — the outer `{}` is JSX expression, then `.map()` returns the array, and the `)}` closes the map callback and the `.map` call. Then there's an extra `)`. Let me count the parens:\n\n- `{` — JSX expression open\n- `POSES.map(` — function call open\n- `p =>` — arrow function\n- `<div ...>` — JSX\n- `</div>` — close JSX\n- `)` — closes `map(` \n- `}` — closes JSX expression `{`\n- `)` — EXTRA!\n\nThere's an extra `)` at the end. Let me fix it:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ed2ed4bb-fc35-4e28-b9d4-137b7176a868","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/sprites/SpriteSheetGenerator.tsx","edits":[{"oldText":"{POSES.map(p => <div key={p} style={{flex:\"0 0 96px\",minWidth:96,fontSize:7,color:\"#1E1C38\",letterSpacing:2,textAlign:\"center\"}}>{p}</div>))}","newText":"{POSES.map(p => <div key={p} style={{flex:\"0 0 96px\",minWidth:96,fontSize:7,color:\"#1E1C38\",letterSpacing:2,textAlign:\"center\"}}>{p}</div>)}"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/sprites/SpriteSheetGenerator.tsx\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"{POSES.map(p => <div key={p} style={{flex:\\\"0 0 96px\\\",minWidth:96,fontSize:7,color:\\\"#1E1C38\\\",letterSpacing:2,textAlign:\\\"center\\\"}}>{p}</div>))}\", \"newText\": \"{POSES.map(p => <div key={p} style={{flex:\\\"0 0 96px\\\",minWidth:96,fontSize:7,color:\\\"#1