{"type":"message","id":"d1cfaecb","parentId":"54a7419d","timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:31:30.237Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The dev server is running and `/sprites` returns 200. But Andre hasn't sent the actual PNG files yet — he said he'll share via Telegraph. The file he attached was the sprite generator code itself (which I've already integrated).\n\nLet me check if maybe the sprites were included as Telegraph links I missed:\n\nLooking at the message again carefully — Andre said \"newsprites\" followed by the TSX file attachment, then described replacing sprite files. The actual PNG files haven't been sent yet. He said he's going to share them via Telegraph.\n\nI should wait for the actual sprite PNG files before replacing anything. Let me acknowledge this to Andre.\n\n[[reply_to_current]] The sprite generator is live at `/sprites` — I integrated the code you sent and pushed to main. Build is clean.\n\nWaiting for the actual PNG sprite files via Telegraph — drop the links and I'll replace them in assets, update any dimensional refs, and verify all pages render correctly. 🐒"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":293,"output":209,"cacheRead":112384,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":112886,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780299051390,"responseId":"gen-1780299051-HqsT6bs8mhgYdqK7saTo"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6dfc0855-5beb-4c13-af27-22af7656a476","parentId":"d1cfaecb","timestamp":"2026-06-01T07:31:32.035Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The dev server is running and `/sprites` returns 200. But Andre hasn't sent the actual PNG files yet — he said he'll share via Telegraph. The file he attached was the sprite generator code itself (which I've already integrated).\n\nLet me check if maybe the sprites were included as Telegraph links I missed:\n\nLooking at the message again carefully — Andre said \"newsprites\" followed by the TSX file attachment, then described replacing sprite files. The actual PNG files haven't been sent yet. He said he's going to share them via Telegraph.\n\nI should wait for the actual sprite PNG files before replacing anything. Let me acknowledge this to Andre.\n\n The sprite generator is live at `/sprites` — I integrated the code you sent and pushed to main. Build is clean.\n\nWaiting for the actual PNG sprite files via Telegraph — drop the links and I'll replace them in assets, update any dimensional refs, and verify all pages render correctly. 🐒"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"total":0,"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":0,"total_tokens":0,"cache":{"read":0,"write":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780299092031}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b6badd5","parentId":"6dfc0855-5beb-4c13-af27-22af7656a476","timestamp":"2026-06-01T12:48:47.021Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The Kanban progress bar is a fake CSS animation — it doesn't reflect \nreal work. A task can sit \"In Progress\" for hours with the bar stuck \nat the same position. Fix this.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nHOW THE PROGRESS BAR SHOULD WORK\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. REAL AGENT ACTIVITY — The progress bar should reflect actual work, \n   not a CSS animation. When an agent is actively working on a task, \n   it should update the task's progress in the data.\n\n2. PROGRESS UPDATES — When an agent starts or continues work on a task, \n   it should update:\n   - `progress`: 0-100 (percentage complete)\n   - `lastActivity`: timestamp of last action\n   - `currentStep`: short description of what it's doing right now \n     (e.g. \"Running build...\", \"Writing tests...\", \"Reviewing code...\")\n\n3. STALE DETECTION — If a task has been In Progress for more than \n   30 minutes with NO update to lastActivity:\n   - Show \"⚠️ Stalled — no activity for X min\" \n   - Move progress bar to a warning color (amber)\n   - Send a Telegram alert\n   - If stalled for 2+ hours, auto-move back to Backlog with a note\n\n4. VISUAL CHANGES TO THE KANBAN CARD:\n   - Show currentStep text below the task title\n   - Show \"Last active: X min ago\" timestamp\n   - Progress bar color: green (actively working), amber (stalled), \n     grey (no activity yet)\n   - If progress is 100%, move to Awaiting Review (not Done — you \n     still need to verify)\n\n5. AGENT REQUIREMENT — When an agent works on a task, it MUST:\n   - Update the task's progress and currentStep at least every 5 \n     minutes while working\n   - If it stops working (timeout, context switch, error), update \n     the task status immediately — don't leave it hanging\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nIMPLEMENTATION\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. Update the Task type to include `progress`, `lastActivity`, and \n   `currentStep` fields\n2. Modify the Kanban card to show real progress instead of CSS \n   animation\n3. Add the stale detection logic (30 min warning, 2 hour auto-return \n   to Backlog)\n4. Update AGENTS.md: agents must update task progress while working\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nCURRENT STUCK TASK\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nBefore building, check: what task is currently In Progress? Is it \nactually being worked on or is it stalled? If stalled, move it back \nto Backlog first, then implement the fix.","timestamp":1780318126891,"idempotencyKey":"94c6945a-69ed-4ed7-b4f3-7259302c0912:user"}}
