old cron jobs replaced with single lightweight daily check\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"errorId\": \"err-cd8044dc-c68b-4113-82f6-d19203937f1a\",\n    \"jobId\": \"cd8044dc-c68b-4113-82f6-d19203937f1a\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-16T01:30:00Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"err-err-31eeb9bf-5402-42d1-b07b-d7f7af5e17c1\",\n    \"title\": \"[Investigate] Activity Summary: All models failed (6): openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-day-stealth. (rate_limit) | openrouter/openrouter/free: 429 Provider returned error (rate_limit) | openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-min. (rate_limit) | openrouter/google/gemma-4-26b-a4b-it:free: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-day. Add 10 credits to unlock 1000 free model requests per day (rate_limit) | openrouter/google/gemma-4-31b-it:free: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-day. Add 10 credits to unlock 1000 free model requests per day (rate_limit) | openrouter/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-day. Add 10 credits to unlock 1000 free model requests per day (rate_limit)\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Auto-created from Scheduler Error Feed.\\nCron job: Activity Summary (31eeb9bf-5402-42d1-b07b-d7f7af5e17c1)\\nError: FallbackSummaryError: All models failed (6): openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-day-stealth. (rate_limit) | openrouter/openrouter/free: 429 Provider returned error (rate_limit) | openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash:free: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-min. (rate_limit) | openrouter/google/gemma-4-26b-a4b-it:free: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-day. Add 10 credits to unlock 1000 free model requests per day (rate_limit) | openrouter/google/gemma-4-31b-it:free: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-day. Add 10 credits to unlock 1000 free model requests per day (rate_limit) | openrouter/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free: 429 Rate limit exceeded: free-models-per-day. Add 10 credits to unlock 1000 free model requests per day (rate_limit)\\nConsecutive errors: 1\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T00:08:26.852Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-created from error feed for Activity Summary\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T01:30:00Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"space-monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Resolved — old cron jobs replaced with single lightweight daily check\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"errorId\": \"err-31eeb9bf-5402-42d1-b07b-d7f7af5e17c1\",\n    \"jobId\": \"31eeb9bf-5402-42d1-b07b-d7f7af5e17c1\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-16T01:30:00Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mp8p7in6-33ju\",\n    \"title\": \"Dashboard Animation\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:17.644Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"note\": \"The living office animations aren't rendering despite being deployed. \\nI need this area to be alive — imagine a fish tank. The station is the \\ntank, the agents are the fish, tasks are the food. Fish don't sit still \\nin stagnant water. They swim, drift, feed, interact. The tank is always \\nalive even when nothing's happening.\\n\\nIf the current approach works, fix it. If it doesn't, rebuild it.\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nPHASE 1: DIAGNOSTIC\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\nAnswer with evidence, not assumptions:\\n\\n1. How are sprites rendered? Canvas? DOM <img> tags? SVG? React components?\\n   Paste the relevant 20 lines from StationRoom.tsx.\\n\\n2. How are animations applied? CSS keyframes? Framer Motion? \\n   requestAnimationFrame? Canvas draw loop?\\n\\n3. Open browser DevTools (F12) → Elements → find a sprite element.\\n   - Does it have animation/transition/transform CSS properties?\\n   - Console tab: any JavaScript errors?\\n   - Network tab: are the CSS files loading? Search for \\\"sprite-working\\\" \\n     or \\\"ambient-pulse\\\" in loaded stylesheets.\\n\\n4. What data is reaching StationRoom? Console.log agent name, status, \\n   currentAction. Are values changing or stuck?\\n\\n5. Are the CSS classes (sprite-working, sprite-sleeping, ambient-pulse, \\n   ambient-flicker) actually on the DOM elements? Do the CSS rules exist?\\n\\nReport findings before making changes.\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nPHASE 2: IF CSS ANIMATIONS WORK — FIX THE BUG\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\nIf the diagnostic shows animations are present but not firing:\\n- Fix whatever's blocking them (missing class application, data not \\n  updating, SSR vs client mismatch)\\n- Force a visible test: Space Monkey with green \\\"TEST\\\" bubble, \\n  Systems Engineer walking across the floorplan\\n- Verify in browser DevTools that animation properties are active\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nPHASE 3: IF CSS ANIMATIONS DON'T WORK — CANVAS FISH TANK\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\nIf CSS animations are fundamentally unreliable, rebuild using a single \\nHTML5 Canvas with a requestAnimationFrame loop — like an actual fish \\ntank simulation.\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n- One full-size Canvas element fills the Spacestation area\\n- Room backgrounds drawn once as a static layer\\n- Agent sprites drawn on top as an animated layer\\n- Single requestAnimationFrame loop at 60fps:\\n  1. Clear sprite layer\\n  2. Calculate each agent's position based on state\\n  3. Draw sprites at current positions\\n  4. Repeat\\n\\nAGENT BEHAVIOUR (like fish in a tank):\\n- IDLE: gentle drift within home room (slow random movement in a \\n  small radius, like a fish hovering). Changes direction every 5-8 \\n  seconds. Never completely still.\\n- WORKING: moves to task location within room. Small rapid movements \\n  like a fish feeding. Status bubble appears.\\n- WALKING: linear interpolation from current position to target room. \\n  Walking sprite frames cycle. ~2 seconds to cross between rooms.\\n- SLEEPING: sinks slightly lower in the room. Minimal drift. Small \\n  \\\"zzz\\\" particles float upward and fade.\\n- COLLABORATING: two agents move close together, face each other. \\n  Small dashes or particles flow between them.\\n\\nALWAYS-ON MOVEMENT:\\n- Even when all agents are idle, they DRIFT. Not static. Not frozen.\\n- Like a real fish tank — no one stares at it and wonders \\\"is it on?\\\"\\n- Subtle but constant. The eye catches the movement.\\n- Room ambience (radar, sparks, lanterns, monitors) continues as \\n  background animation on the static layer.\\n\\nPERFORMANCE:\\n- GPU-composited canvas (transform: translateZ(0))\\n- requestAnimationFrame pauses when tab hidden (Page Visibility API)\\n- Agent positions updated each frame, sprites drawn via \\n  ctx.drawImage() with sprite sheet selection based on state\\n- Target: 60fps, zero layout reflow\\n\\nDEBUG VISIBILITY:\\n- Add a small frame counter in the corner of the canvas\\n- Add agent position log (x, y, state) that updates visibly\\n- This proves the animation loop is running\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nDELIVERABLE\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\nAfter Phase 1 diagnostic:\\n- Report what rendering method is used\\n- Report what animation method is used\\n- Report whether animations are present in the DOM but not visible, \\n  or completely absent\\n\\nThen proceed to Phase 2 or Phase 3 based on findings.\\n\\nIf Phase 3 (canvas rebuild):\\n- The fish tank should be visibly alive within one session\\n- I should see agents drifting even when idle\\n- I should see the frame counter ticking to prove the loop runs\\n- Commit and push when working\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T18:47:19.074Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T18:49:02.286Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T23:42:05.890Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from in_progress to backlog\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T23:42:06.972Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T23:42:09.343Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from in_progress to backlog\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-16T23:42:11.636Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-17T21:57:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — task was stuck for 20h with no progress. Will be picked up by dispatcher.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-19T02:28:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"dispatcher\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress by Task Dispatcher\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:17.644Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from in_progress to done\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:17.644Z\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-05-19T02:28:00.000Z\",\n    \"summary\": \"Completed by monkey. Last action: started — Status changed from backlog to in_progress by Task Dispatcher\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"err-err-7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"title\": \"[Investigate] Task Dispatcher: cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Auto-created from Scheduler Error Feed.\\nCron job: Task Dispatcher (7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f)\\nError: cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)\\nConsecutive errors: 1\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-18T14:21:02.512Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-created from error feed for Task Dispatcher\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:18.581Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from in_progress to done\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"errorId\": \"err-7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"jobId\": \"7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:18.581Z\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-19T08:05:18.581Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"summary\": \"Completed by monkey.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"err-err-7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f\",\n    \"title\": \"[Investigate] Task Dispatcher: session file changed while embedded prompt lock was released: /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/076895dd-43e4-428f-ae33-ec91ab0df26a.jsonl\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Auto-created from Scheduler Error Feed.\\nCron job: Task Dispatcher (7e2c02bf-ae83-44be-8012-adfcdd42f42f)\\nError: EmbeddedAttemptSessionTakeoverError: session file changed while embedded prompt lock was released: /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/076895dd-43e4-428f-ae33-ec91ab0