ation Check\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T13:30:35.812Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from in_progress to backlog\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T13:40:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"dispatcher\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress by Task Dispatcher\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T16:35:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — task stale for ~3h with no progress update. Will be re-picked up by dispatcher or main session.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Cron healthy, marking done\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"errorId\": \"err-dae7406b-ec78-4752-ba93-91bc62541f7d\",\n    \"jobId\": \"dae7406b-ec78-4752-ba93-91bc62541f7d\",\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-05-21T13:40:00.000Z\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-21T17:25:00.000Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"summary\": \"Resolved — Daily Station Check cron is healthy (status: ok). Timeout was transient. No further action needed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mprfp410-oz8b\",\n    \"title\": \"Settings patch adjust\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Settings page fixes confirmed. The version, status, crons, and port \\nlabels are all correct now. \\n\\nOne final check: the Run Backup button calls openclaw-backup-quick.sh. \\nWe know this script targets /Volumes/Public/ which may not be mounted \\n(we hit the SMB permission wall). Confirm: does the button show a \\nfriendly error if the backup target isn't available, or does it fail \\nsilently?\\n\\nIf it fails silently, add a check to the backup script that alerts \\nif the target isn't mounted — write to mount-alert.txt so Telegram \\npicks it up.\\n\\nAfter that, the Settings page audit is complete. Station is stable.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-29T21:28:41.124Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-29T21:28:42.219Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-29T22:44:02.954998+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Settings page audit complete. All 5 fixes applied: version from CLI status, gateway status from CLI, active crons from cron list, port 3000, restart gateway via launchctl. Backup script now checks for mounted target and returns friendly error.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-29T22:44:02.954998+00:00\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-05-29T21:28:42.219Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-29T22:44:02.954998+00:00\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-104\",\n    \"title\": \"Create app shortcut for Mission Control\",\n    \"assignee\": \"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-105\",\n    \"title\": \"Fix task persistence — saveTasks not writing to disk\",\n    \"assignee\": \"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n    \"note\": \"Fixed with direct fetch API to /api/save-tasks endpoint\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-112\",\n    \"title\": \"Control UI bridge — pull data from localhost:18789\",\n    \"assignee\": \"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"30m ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"30m ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-113\",\n    \"title\": \"Quick Actions expansion\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"30m ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"30m ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-114\",\n    \"title\": \"Cloud storage planning + cron job architecture\",\n    \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"30m ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"30m ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-101\",\n    \"title\": \"Set up Mission Control Dashboard\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"3h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"3h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-102\",\n    \"title\": \"Configure WD MyCloud backup automation\",\n    \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"3h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"3h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-103\",\n    \"title\": \"Implement Karpathy LLM Wiki pattern\",\n    \"assignee\": \"archivist\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"3h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"3h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mp7cbyxz-0ztq\",\n    \"title\": \"Error Feed — behaviour review and fix.\",\n    \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n    \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Error Feed — behaviour review and fix.\\n\\nThe error feed currently has Investigate / Resolved / Skip buttons but \\nthe workflow is confusing. Here's how it should actually work:\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nCORRECT ERROR FEED WORKFLOW\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\n1. A cron job fails → error appears in the Error Feed tab with a \\n   \\\"NEW\\\" badge\\n\\n2. I click \\\"Investigate\\\" → \\n   - The error status changes to \\\"IN PROGRESS\\\" \\n   - A corresponding task is automatically created in the Tasks \\n     section under \\\"In Progress\\\" so the crew knows to work on it\\n   - The error stays visible in the feed with an in-progress indicator\\n   - The button changes to show \\\"Resolved\\\" and \\\"Skip\\\"\\n\\n3. The crew fixes the underlying issue. The cron job runs successfully \\n   on its next scheduled run →\\n   - The error automatically clears from the Error Feed\\n   - The linked task in the Tasks section moves to \\\"Done\\\"\\n   - No manual \\\"Resolved\\\" click needed — the system verified the fix\\n\\n4. If I click \\\"Resolved\\\" manually →\\n   - For when I've verified the fix myself\\n   - Error disappears from the feed\\n   - Linked task moves to Done\\n\\n5. If I click \\\"Skip\\\" →\\n   - For known non-critical issues I'm choosing to ignore\\n   - Error disappears from the feed\\n   - No task is created\\n\\n6. If the same job fails again later →\\n   - A NEW error appears (not the old one reopened)\\n   - Fresh timestamp, fresh status\\n   - Does NOT resurrect the old skipped/resolved error\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nKEY RULES\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\n- Errors should NOT show \\\"Completed\\\" with an \\\"In Progress\\\" flag \\n  at the same time (current bug)\\n- When a cron job succeeds after being in error state, the error \\n  should auto-clear — the system verified the fix\\n- The \\\"Investigate\\\" button creates a task in the Tasks board so \\n  work is tracked\\n- The error feed reflects REALITY: if the job is still failing, \\n  the error stays. If it succeeds, the error goes away.\\n- The cron job entry in the Scheduler list should show an error \\n  badge ONLY while there's an active unresolved error\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nWHAT TO FIX NOW\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\n1. Fix the double-status bug (no more \\\"Completed\\\" + \\\"In Progress\\\" \\n   showing simultaneously)\\n2. Wire Investigate button to auto-create a task in the Tasks board\\n3. Wire cron job success to auto-clear the corresponding error\\n4. Wire cron job error badge to auto-clear when error is resolved\\n5. Confirm Skip behaviour works as described above\\n6. Test the full flow end-to-end\\n\\nReport what the current behaviour actually is, then fix it to \\nmatch this spec.  [auto-dispatched 2026-06-01 11:53]\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T19:59:05.639Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T19:59:07.177Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T08:00:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (started 2026-05-15T20:36 with no progress)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T09:00:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — stale (started May 15, no progress)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T09:43:21.368763+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (397h with no progress update)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T11:00:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — task was stuck in in_progress with no startedAt, likely from incomplete prior dispatch\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T11:30:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset to backlog — task has been stalled since May 15 with no progress. Note: keeps flipping back to in_progress when MC frontend saves stale state.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-01T11:30:00.000Z\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mp7d3s9w-1lmf\",\n    \"title\": \"Task Completion — summary and visibility improvement.\",\n    \"assignee\": \"archivist\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Task Completion — summary and visibility improvement.\\n\\nThe auto-move from In Progress to Done works well. But when a task \\nmoves to Done, I can't tell WHAT was actually done. The card just \\nsays \\\"Done\\\" with no context.\\n\\nFix:\\n\\n1. When a task completes and auto-moves to Done, the card must \\n   include a brief summary of what was accomplished. This summary \\n   should be:\\n   - Written by the agent that completed the task\\n   - 1-3 sentences describing the actual outcome\\n   - Stored on the task card itself, visible in the Kanban view\\n   - Also visible when I click \\\"More Details\\\" on the card\\n\\n2. The \\\"More Details\\\" view on any Done card should show:\\n   - Original task description\\n   - Completion summary (what was actually done)\\n   - Which agent completed it\\n   - Timestamp of completion\\n   - Any relevant links or artifacts produced (files changed, \\n     commits made, etc.)\\n\\n3. In the Kanban view, a Done card should show at minimum:\\n   - Task title\\n   - One-line completion summary (truncated if needed)\\n   - \\\"Done by [Agent] • [time]\\\"\\n\\n4. If the task was created manually by me (not auto-generated from \\n   an error or cron job), the agent who picks it up should write \\n   the completion summary before moving it to Done. If no summary \\n   is written, the task should NOT auto-move — it should stay In \\n   Progress with a flag: \\\"Awaiting completion summary.\\\"\\n\\nThis applies to ALL tasks going forward. Retroactively fixing old \\nDone tasks is optional — only if quick.\\n\\nReport your approach before implementing.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:20:43.364Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:20:45.084Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:36:50.973Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from done to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T08:00:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (started 2026-05-15T20:36 with no progress)\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-01T08:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"progress\": 40\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-115\",\n    \"title\": \"GitHub integration — push MC to GitHub for version control\",\n    \"assignee\": \"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Auto-dispatched by work dispatcher cron\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": false,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:27:34.473Z\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-05-14T15:21:38.481Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"inc-INC-004-mp5dot1f\",\n    \"title\": \"[Dispatch] Switch to cron expression\",\n    \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Replace everyMs schedule with cron '0 3 * * *' in Europe/London tz\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:12:14.861Z\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"inc-INC-001-mp5b66tk\",\n    \"title\": \"[Dispatch] Add integrity check to heartbeat\",\n    \"assignee\": \"archivist\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Add index health check to HEARTBEAT.md so corruption is caught early\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:12:14.861Z\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"inc-INC-002-mp5b37v4\",\n    \"title\": \"[Dispatch] Set up automated daily backups\",\n    \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Configure cron job for daily 3am backup runs\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:12:14.861Z\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"inc-INC-002-mp5b36xd\",\n    \"title\": \"[Dispatch] Decommission old mount path\",\n    \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Remove references to /Volumes/WD-MyCloud/OpenClaw from scripts\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:12:14.861Z\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"inc-INC-001-mp5b2jw2\",\n    \"title\": \"[Dispatch] Verify search accuracy\",\n    \"assignee\": \"archivist\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Run test queries against rebuilt index to confirm all entries are findable\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:12:14.861Z\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"inc-INC-001-mp58a9ii\",\n    \"title\": \"[Incident] Add integrity check to heartbeat\",\n    \"assignee\": \"archivist\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Add index health check to HEARTBEAT.md so corruption is caught early\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:12:14.861Z\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"inc-INC-001-mp58973d\",\n    \"title\": \"[Incident] Verify search accuracy\",\n    \"assignee\": \"archivist\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Run test queries against rebuilt index to confirm all entries are findable\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:12:14.861Z\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-118\",\n    \"title\": \"Build work dispatcher — auto-pull from backlog when idle\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-119\",\n    \"title\": \"Dashboard redesign — 3-column layout with live activity feed\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Redesign Mission Control home page: Left=live activity feed, Center=Spacestation rooms, Right=system stats/quick actions. Rename from Spacestation to Dashboard.\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-14T15:12:14.861Z\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  }\n]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780318151150}}
{"type":"message","id":"b584576e","parentId":"46c587ba","timestamp":"2026-06-01T12:49:11.153Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"646f6383-39e3-4657-9aea-0f4fcb75ad16","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { useState, useCallback, useEffect, useRef } from \"react\";\nimport { createFileRoute } from \"@tanstack/react-router\";\nimport { PageHeader, Pill } from \"@/components/PageHeader\";\nimport { CREW, getCrew } from \"@/lib/crew\";\nimport { getTasks } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { Task } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\n\nasync function saveTasksToDisk(tasks: Task[]): Promise<{ ok: boolean }> {\n  const res = await fetch(\"/api/save-tasks\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify(tasks),\n  });\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    let errMsg = \"Save failed\";\n    try { const err = await res.json(); errMsg = err.error || errMsg; } catch { /* ignore */ }\n    throw new Error(errMsg);\n  }\n  return res.json();\n}\n\nasync function dispatchTaskToQueue(task: { taskId: string; title: string; assignee: string }): Promise<{ ok: boolean; queueId?: string }> {\n  const res = await fetch(\"/api/dispatch\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify(task),\n  });\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    let errMsg = \"Dispatch failed\";\n    try { const err = await res.json(); errMsg = err.error || errMsg; } catch { /* ignore */ }\n    throw new Error(errMsg);\n  }\n  return res.json();\n}\nimport { Plus, X, User, FileText, ChevronDown, Send, Pencil, Trash2, Clock, User as UserIcon, CheckCircle } from \"lucide-react\";\n\n// ── Auto-move configuration ────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst AUTO_COMPLETE_DELAY_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000; // 5 minutes\nimport { loadState, saveState } from \"@/lib/persist\";\n\nexport const Route = createFileRoute(\"/tasks\")({\n  head: () => ({ meta: [{ title: \"Tasks — Mission Control\" }] }),\n  loader: async () => {\n    try {\n      const tasks = await getTasks();\n      console.log(\"[tasks loader] Loaded\", tasks.length, \"tasks\");\n      return tasks;\n    } catch (err) {\n      console.error(\"[tasks loader] Error:\", err);\n      return [];\n    }\n  },\n  component: TasksPage,\n  errorComponent: ({ error }) => {\n    console.error(\"[tasks route] Error:\", error);\n    return (\n      <div className=\"rounded-xl border border-destructive/40 bg-destructive/10 px-6 py-14 text-center\">\n        <div className=\"font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.25em] text-destructive\">— LOADER ERROR —</div>\n        <div className=\"mt-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground\">Failed to load tasks. Check console for details.</div>\n        <div className=\"mt-2 font-mono text-[10px] text-muted-foreground/50\">{String(error)}</div>\n      </div>\n    );\n  },\n});\n\nconst COLS: { key: Task[\"status\"]; label: string; accent: string }[] = [\n  { key: \"backlog\", label: \"Backlog\", accent: \"text-muted-foreground\" },\n  { key: \"in_progress\", label: \"In Progress\", accent: \"text-[oklch(0.85_0.12_295)]\" },\n  { key: \"done\", label: \"Done\", accent: \"text-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\" },\n  { key: \"awaiting_review\", label: \"Awaiting Review\", accent: \"text-[oklch(0.85_0.12_225)]\" },\n];\n\nfunction generateId(): string {\n  return `task-${Date.now().toString(36)}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 6)}`;\n}\n\n// ── New Task Modal ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction NewTaskModal({ onClose, onAdd }: { onClose: () => void; onAdd: (t: Task) => void }) {\n  const [title, setTitle] = useState(\"\");\n  const [assignee, setAssignee] = useState(\"monkey\");\n  const [priority, setPriority] = useState<\"P1\" | \"P2\" | \"P3\" | \"P4\">(\"P3\");\n  const [note, setNote] = useState(\"\");\n  const [submitting, setSubmitting] = useState(false);\n\n  const handleSubmit = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!title.trim() || submitting) return;\n    setSubmitting(true);\n    const task: Task = {\n      id: generateId(),\n      title: title.trim(),\n      assignee,\n      status: \"backlog\",\n      priority: \"P3\" as const,\n      ts: \"just now\",\n      note: note.trim() || undefined,\n      history: [{ ts: new Date().toISOString(), action: \"created\" as const, actor: assignee, details: \"Task created\" }],\n    };\n    onAdd(task);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":25,"aggregated":"import { useState, useCallback, useEffect, useRef } from \"react\";\nimport { createFileRoute } from \"@tanstack/react-router\";\nimport { PageHeader, Pill } from \"@/components/PageHeader\";\nimport { CREW, getCrew } from \"@/lib/crew\";\nimport { getTasks } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { Task } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\n\nasync function saveTasksToDisk(tasks: Task[]): Promise<{ ok: boolean }> {\n  const res = await fetch(\"/api/save-tasks\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify(tasks),\n  });\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    let errMsg = \"Save failed\";\n    try { const err = await res.json(); errMsg = err.error || errMsg; } catch { /* ignore */ }\n    throw new Error(errMsg);\n  }\n  return res.json();\n}\n\nasync function dispatchTaskToQueue(task: { taskId: string; title: string; assignee: string }): Promise<{ ok: boolean; queueId?: string }> {\n  const res = await fetch(\"/api/dispatch\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify(task),\n  });\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    let errMsg = \"Dispatch failed\";\n    try { const err = await res.json(); errMsg = err.error || errMsg; } catch { /* ignore */ }\n    throw new Error(errMsg);\n  }\n  return res.json();\n}\nimport { Plus, X, User, FileText, ChevronDown, Send, Pencil, Trash2, Clock, User as UserIcon, CheckCircle } from \"lucide-react\";\n\n// ── Auto-move configuration ────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst AUTO_COMPLETE_DELAY_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000; // 5 minutes\nimport { loadState, saveState } from \"@/lib/persist\";\n\nexport const Route = createFileRoute(\"/tasks\")({\n  head: () => ({ meta: [{ title: \"Tasks — Mission Control\" }] }),\n  loader: async () => {\n    try {\n      const tasks = await getTasks();\n      console.log(\"[tasks loader] Loaded\", tasks.length, \"tasks\");\n      return tasks;\n    } catch (err) {\n      console.error(\"[tasks loader] Error:\", err);\n      return [];\n    }\n  },\n  component: TasksPage,\n  errorComponent: ({ error }) => {\n    console.error(\"[tasks route] Error:\", error);\n    return (\n      <div className=\"rounded-xl border border-destructive/40 bg-destructive/10 px-6 py-14 text-center\">\n        <div className=\"font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.25em] text-destructive\">— LOADER ERROR —</div>\n        <div className=\"mt-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground\">Failed to load tasks. Check console for details.</div>\n        <div className=\"mt-2 font-mono text-[10px] text-muted-foreground/50\">{String(error)}</div>\n      </div>\n    );\n  },\n});\n\nconst COLS: { key: Task[\"status\"]; label: string; accent: string }[] = [\n  { key: \"backlog\", label: \"Backlog\", accent: \"text-muted-foreground\" },\n  { key: \"in_progress\", label: \"In Progress\", accent: \"text-[oklch(0.85_0.12_295)]\" },\n  { key: \"done\", label: \"Done\", accent: \"text-[oklch(0.88_0.18_145)]\" },\n  { key: \"awaiting_review\", label: \"Awaiting Review\", accent: \"text-[oklch(0.85_0.12_225)]\" },\n];\n\nfunction generateId(): string {\n  return `task-${Date.now().toString(36)}-${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 6)}`;\n}\n\n// ── New Task Modal ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction NewTaskModal({ onClose, onAdd }: { onClose: () => void; onAdd: (t: Task) => void }) {\n  const [title, setTitle] = useState(\"\");\n  const [assignee, setAssignee] = useState(\"monkey\");\n  const [priority, setPriority] = useState<\"P1\" | \"P2\" | \"P3\" | \"P4\">(\"P3\");\n  const [note, setNote] = useState(\"\");\n  const [submitting, setSubmitting] = useState(false);\n\n  const handleSubmit = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!title.trim() || submitting) return;\n    setSubmitting(true);\n    const task: Task = {\n      id: generateId(),\n      title: title.trim(),\n      assignee,\n      status: \"backlog\",\n      priority: \"P3\" as const,\n      ts: \"just now\",\n      note: note.trim() || undefined,\n      history: [{ ts: new Date().toISOString(), action: \"created\" as const, actor: assignee, details: \"Task created\" }],\n    };\n    onAdd(task);","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780318151153}}
